AutomationPackConfiguration.DisplayName: Intelligent Automation for Cloud Extension Samples
AutomationPackConfiguration.Description:
This automation pack contains programming examples to be used in concert with Cisco Intelligent Automation for Cloud.
All sample code is provided by Cisco for illustrative purposes as a foundation upon which to extend. These examples have not been thoroughly tested under all conditions.
Sample code should be copied and modified appropriately before used in a production environment.

AutomatioPackInfo.Description: This automation pack contains common Orchestrator processes and objects for cloud infrastructure orchestration.
This automation pack contains Orchestrator processes, Portal services and Portal portlets that implement basic IaaS cloud.
This automation pack will import the default content to support other automation packs.

AdapterInfo.Description: Provides core functionality that is required by the Cisco Process Orchestrator Server.
Provides activities to access Cisco Prime Service Catalog service items and service requests.
Provides activity to call Web Service methods.
Provides access to Windows activities and objects.
